The paper deals with a geometric problem of dominance relations among stochastic points, which suggests the category cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The problem involves probability and counting, which are typical topics in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The paper also mentions the complexity of the problem, which indicates the category cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Finally, the paper discusses a variant of the problem that involves orthogonal bases, which is related to cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
